analysis: The documents in this cluster primarily concern the designation of various international organizations as public international organizations, granting them certain privileges, exemptions, and immunities under the International Organizations Immunities Act. The documents also cover the extension of privileges and immunities to permanent observer missions and their members, as well as the revocation of previous designations. The common theme is the legal and administrative actions taken by the US government to define and regulate its relationship with international bodies.
title: International Organizations: Privileges and Immunities
